			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here's my idea on how to fix Sparky...yes it's a cross post.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Tweelis Twitchydigits wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Child of Ro sits in my spell book....and has only been used once. Even with MoE it's a useless pet except against greenie farming (even then I use epic). I'd recommend giving the pet 8 spell slots just like any other caster. Have two fire based DD, two cold based DD, two magic based DD, and two lure - all of the appropriate level for the pet (ie, level 62 pet would have nukes up to what a level 62 wizard would have). 
<br />

<br />
Purposefully do NOT give them concussion type spells but do have mobs get upset with pets (and their owners) for overnuking just like some wizards. This would force the pet owner to carefully control their pet in order to not steal aggro from the group/raid MT. 
<br />

<br />
Couple this spell line up with an appropriate mana pool. Rough guesses here but something along the lines of: 
<br />
DPoC focused: 3500 point mana pool. 
<br />
MoDarkness: 4000 
<br />
MoEternity: 4500 
<br />
Ritual Summoning: 5000 
<br />
MoDiscord: 5500 
<br />

<br />
Third would have different hotkeys for the fire pet. Still have a general /pet attack but also make it so if we're fighting mobs with certain resists allow us to have a /pet castcold /pet castfire /pet castmagic. Players already do this so it would make sense that if we wanted Sparky to cast only cold based nukes in The Kingdom of Wind we could tell it to. 
<br />

<br />
A further possible AA to add to this would be something like giving sparky the ability to memorize and cast AE spells. A new command like /pet mempbae and a /pet castpbae at the first level of mastery. Second level of mastery would be /pet memrain and /pet castrain. 
<br />

<br />
Even if the pet spell lineup was reduced by 5-10 levels, I believe it would make the pet more effective than it currently is.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Scaling this for the OoW pets would work nicely as well.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=402042">Tweelis</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
